ProMED-mail
<promed@promed.org>
[The outbreak of falciparum malaria in the Dominican Republic 1999/2000 was
in the end thought to be due to migrant construction workers from Haiti
acting as asymptomatic carriers. It is therefore interesting to note in
this message that the hotel was close to a construction site. Despite this
so far single case, the risk of acquiring malaria in the Dominican Republic
is still very low. - Mod.EP
.............ep/pg/es
